<ext_description linkend="Appearance_assignment_mim.styled_curve">
The <b>styled_curve</b> rule ensures that a <express_ref linkend="presentation_appearance_schema:ir_express:presentation_appearance_schema.styled_item"/>

 of a <express_ref linkend="geometry_schema:ir_express:geometry_schema.curve"/>

 is defined by a single <express_ref linkend="presentation_appearance_schema:ir_express:presentation_appearance_schema.curve_style"/>. 
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Appearance_assignment_mim.styled_curve.wr:WR1">
there shall be no instance of <express_ref linkend="presentation_appearance_schema:ir_express:presentation_appearance_schema.styled_item"/>

 of a <express_ref linkend="geometry_schema:ir_express:geometry_schema.curve"/>

 that has not exactly one <express_ref linkend="presentation_appearance_schema:ir_express:presentation_appearance_schema.curve_style"/>. 
</ext_description>
